web-player.pigeon.help-cards.listen-offl: Download your music in Lossless to listen in our highest quality while you’re offline. Update download quality in Settings.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.connect-exp: The best way to listen in Lossless is with Spotify Connect. Just play a song, then tap {0} at the bottom of the screen to select a device and control your music straight from the app.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.bluetooth-d: Using Bluetooth will affect Lossless listening
Most Bluetooth devices can play music quality better Very high, but don’t fully support lossless sound. Lossless is best enjoyed over Spotify Connect speakers and/or wired devices.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.opt-out-of-: Change your settings for a smoother listening experience

You’ve disabled the auto-adjust quality feature in Settings. This means you might experience interruptions in your listening experience when you have poor internet bandwidth. You can turn this feature on in Settings.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.poor-bandwi: Looks like your internet bandwidth is having a hard time supporting Lossless right now. Try checking your connection or switching to a different network.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.default-to-: Change your settings to stream Lossless

Nothing is worse than when a song skips. That’s why we automatically adjust you from Lossless to a lower audio quality if your bandwidth is poor. You can turn off the auto-adjust quality feature in Settings.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.need-to-red: Re-download your songs to play them in Lossless

The songs you’ve downloaded aren’t currently in Lossless. If you want to listen to them in Lossless, you’ll need to re-download them. Just remember, Lossless song files are big and can take up a lot of storage. You can change the audio quality of your downloads in Settings.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.lossless-un: We’re sorry, this track isn’t in lossless yet.
web-player.pigeon.help-cards.update-sett: Change your audio quality settings to stream in Lossless
In your Settings, you set your music to play at very high or lower. To change this, go to Settings and select Lossless.
